headline: Tracking the Evolving Cummins Narrative After Shifting Analyst Views
summary: Cummins stock has seen a modest uptick in its fair value estimate to about $532 per share as analysts grow more confident in the durability of earnings and the long term boost from data center power demand. A slightly lower discount rate and essentially unchanged revenue growth assumptions together signal a fine tuning of expectations rather than a wholesale rethink of the story. Stay tuned to see how you can track these subtle but important narrative shifts as they unfold over time. Analyst...
